parts:
ÓàÉWith a $10 budget on Xbox, your kids have a couple of options to enjoy Minecraft content:ÓàÑÓàÜ

---

### üéÆ Option 1: Purchase Minecoins for In-Game Content

ÓàÉ**Minecoins** are the in-game currency used in Minecraft's Marketplace to buy skins, texture packs, maps, and mini-games.ÓàÑ ÓàÉFor around $10, you can purchase **1,720 Minecoins**, which can be used across Xbox, Windows 10, Nintendo Switch, and mobile devices, provided they're linked to the same Xbox Live account.ÓàÑ ÓàÄciteÓàÇturn0search1ÓàÇturn0search5ÓàÅÓàÜ

ÓàÉYou can purchase Minecoins from various retailers:ÓàÑÓàÜ

- **Walmart**: ÓàÉ[Minecraft Minecoin Pack 1720 Coins - Xbox One (Digital)](https://www.walmart.com/ip/Minecraft-Minecoin-Pack-1720-Coins-Xbox-One-Digital/725568807)ÓàÑ
- **Target**: ÓàÉ[Minecraft: Minecoins 1720 Coins - Xbox One (Digital)](https://www.target.com/p/minecraft-minecoins-1720-coins-xbox-one-digital/-/A-54017734)ÓàÑ
- **Amazon**: ÓàÉ[Minecraft: Minecoins Pack: 1720 Coins [Digital Code]](https://www.amazon.com/Minecraft-Minecoins-Pack-Coins-Digital/dp/B07FYN4SBM)ÓàÑÓàÜ

---

### üïπÔ∏è Option 2: Look for Discounts on Minecraft Base Game

ÓàÉThe standard **Minecraft** game for Xbox typically costs **$19.99**, but it occasionally goes on sale for **$9.99** during promotions.ÓàÑ ÓàÄciteÓàÇturn0search10ÓàÅ ÓàÉIf your kids don't already own the game, it's worth checking the [Xbox Store](https://www.xbox.com/en-US/games/store/minecraft/9MVXMVT8ZKWC) or other retailers like [Target](https://www.target.com/p/minecraft-xbox-series-x-s-xbox-one-digital/-/A-87298224) for current deals.ÓàÑÓàÜ

---

### ‚úÖ Recommendation

- **If your kids already own Minecraft**: ÓàÉPurchasing **1,720 Minecoins** is a great way to enhance their gaming experience with new skins, maps, and mini-games.ÓàÑ
- **If they don't own Minecraft yet**: ÓàÉConsider waiting for a sale to purchase the base game at a discounted price.ÓàÑÓàÜ
